# Cloudflare Pages — security headers applied to every response.
#
# CSP notes:
# - script-src is 'self' (NO 'unsafe-inline') — every page's JS now lives in its own file
#   (S9: homepage -> /assets/home.js, admin -> /assets/admin.js, changelog ->
#   /assets/changelog.js; the app pages already load external scripts). So an injected
#   inline <script> or onX= handler will not execute, even if markup escaping ever slips.
# - style-src keeps 'unsafe-inline' because inline <style> blocks and style="" attributes
#   are still used throughout and there is no build step for per-response style hashes yet.
# - No external origins are needed: every fetch is same-origin (/api/*, /data/*, /app/),
#   and per-trade screenshots are data: URLs (hence img-src 'self' data:). No 'unsafe-eval'.
# - When Stripe checkout lands it redirects (full navigation), so no CSP change is needed;
#   embedded Stripe would need frame-src.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'
